02/03/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha began consultations Thursday (March 1st) with the Democratic Party's ruling coalition allies on the pending government reshuffle. Berisha met with representatives of the New Democracy Party and Party of Human Rights, as well as with Christian Democratic Party, which is expected to joint the cabinet, given its rising popularity in the recent local elections. (Albanian President website, Makfax, Focus - 01/03/07) 
